Interface DocumentProxy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<NamedProxy>, ComparableProxy<NamedProxy>, NamedProxy, Proxy
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConflictCounterExampleProxy, CounterExampleProxy, DualCounterExampleProxy, LoopCounterExampleProxy, ModuleProxy, ModuleSequenceProxy, ProductDESProxy, SafetyCounterExampleProxy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConflictCounterExampleElement, CounterExampleElement, DocumentElement, DualCounterExampleElement, LoopCounterExampleElement, ModuleElement, ModuleSequenceElement, ProductDESElement, SafetyCounterExampleElement

    public interface DocumentProxy
extends NamedProxy

    The interface characterising top-level objects in Waters.

    A document is an object that has its own file representation. Every loaded document should have an associated file name identifying the location from where it has been read, and where it can be written to.

    Author:
    Robi Malik
